Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Identifier: PROCEDURES FOR MONITORING THE USE OF GRANT FUNDS IN THE U.S.
Form990ScheduleIPartIV.ReturnReference: FORM 990, SCHEDULE I, PART I, LINE 2
Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Explanation: ALL GRANTS THE ORGANIZATION ISSUES ARE PARTIAL PAYMENTS FOR MEMBERSHIP FEES FOR A GIRL AND FOR THEM TO ATTEND THE ORGANIZATION'S EVENTS. AN APPLICATION IS COMPLETED INDICATING THE NEED FOR THE ASSISTANCE. THE ASSISTANCE IS THEN PAID DIRECTLY TO THE PROGRAM EVENT OR TROOP MEMBERSHIP. NO FURTHER MONITORING IS NECESSARY.

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: IN GIRL SCOUTS, GIRLS DISCOVER THE FUN, FRIENDSHIP AND POWER OF GIRLS TOGETHER. THROUGH A MYRIAD OF ENRICHING EXPERIENCES, SUCH AS EXTRAORDINARY FIELD TRIPS, OUTDOOR EXPERIENCES, SKILL-BUILDING CLINICS, COMMUNITY SERVICE PROJECTS AND ENVIRONMENTAL STEWARDSHIP, GIRLS GROW COURAGEOUS AND STRONG. GIRL SCOUTING HELPS GIRLS DEVELOP THEIR FULL INDIVIDUAL POTENTIAL; RELATE TO OTHERS WITH INCREASING UNDERSTANDING, SKILL AND RESPECT; DEVELOP VALUES TO GUIDE THEIR ACTIONS AND PROVIDE THE FOUNDATION FOR SOUND DECISION-MAKING; AND CONTRIBUTE TO THE IMPROVEMENT OF SOCIETY THROUGH THEIR ABILITIES, LEADERSHIP SKILLS AND COOPERATION WITH OTHERS.

WITH THE HELP OF ADULT VOLUNTEERS, GIRL SCOUTS OF NE KANSAS & NW MISSOURI DELIVER AGE-APPROPRIATE PROGRAMS THAT ALLOW GIRLS THE OPPORTUNITY TO DEVELOP QUALITIES THAT WILL SERVE THEM ALL THEIR LIVES - SUCH AS LEADERSHIP, STRONG VALUES, SOCIAL CONSCIENCE AND CONVICTION ABOUT THEIR OWN POTENTIAL AND SELF-WORTH. THE ORGANIZATION OFFERS AN UNINTERRUPTED GIRL SCOUT EXPERIENCE FROM THE TIME A GIRL JOINS AS A FIVE-YEAR-OLD DAISY GIRL SCOUT TO WHEN SHE EARNS THE GOLD AWARD, THE HIGHEST AWARD IN GIRL SCOUTING AS A TEEN GIRL SCOUT. GIRLS ARE ORGANIZED INTO TROOPS THAT REFLECT THE FOLLOWING SIX PROGRAM AGE LEVELS: DAISIES, GRADES K-1ST; BROWNIES, GRADES 2ND - 3RD; JUNIORS, GRADES 4TH - 5TH; CADETTES, GRADES 6TH - 8TH; SENIORS, GRADES 9TH - 10TH; AND AMBASSADORS, GRADES 11TH - 12TH. THE GIRL SCOUT PROGRAM FOCUSES ON GIRLS' LEADERSHIP DEVELOPMENT THROUGH TROOP, OUTDOOR ACTIVITIES AND SINGLE-TOPIC EVENTS. GIRLS CAN PARTICIPATE IN ACTIVITIES IN THE AREAS OF FINANCIAL LITERACY, STEM (SCIENCE, TECHNOLOGY, ENGINEERING AND MATH), ENVIRONMENTAL AWARENESS, THE ARTS, COMMUNITY OUTREACH AND HEALTH & WELLNESS. IN ADDITION TO TRADITIONAL TROOPS SUPPORTED BY VOLUNTEERS, GIRL SCOUTS OF NE KANSAS & NW MISSOURI PROVIDES PART-TIME STAFF TO SERVE AS POSITIVE ROLE MODELS TO GIVE GIRLS IN AREAS WHERE A SHORTAGE OF VOLUNTEERISM LIMITS OPPORTUNITIES FOR GIRLS TO PARTICIPATE IN TRADITIONAL TROOPS. GIRL SCOUTS IS THE PREMIER LEADERSHIP ORGANIZATION FOR GIRLS.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11A
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFICER GATHERS INFORMATION TO PREPARE THE FORM 990 TAX RETURN. THIS INFORMATION IS THEN GIVEN TO AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM WHO PREPARES AND REVIEWS THE FORM 990. THE INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM THEN PROVIDES A DRAFT OF THE FORM 990 TO THE SENIOR MANAGEMENT AND AUDIT COMMITTEE MEMBERS FOR COMMENTS AND APPROVAL. PRIOR TO FILING THE FORM 990, ALL GOVERNING MEMBERS RECEIVE A COPY OF THE 990 ALONG WITH A RESPONSE TIME FOR QUESTIONS AND COMMENTS. ALL ISSUES ARE RESOLVED AND THE FORM 990 IS FILED.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: AT THE TIME OF HIRE OR ELECTION (IN THE CASE OF DIRECTORS) AND ANNUALLY THEREAFTER, THE OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, AND KEY EMPLOYEES SHALL PROVIDE THE APPLICABLE CONFLICT OF INTEREST DISCLOSURES WHICH SHALL BE COMPLETED TO IDENTIFY ANY RELATIONSHIPS, POSITIONS, OR CIRCUMSTANCES IN WHICH IT IS BELIEVED A CONFLICT MAY ARISE. IF A CONFLICT ARISES, THE OFFICER, DIRECTOR, OR KEY EMPLOYEE ABSTAINS FROM THE VOTE OF THE CONFLICTED POSITION. ANNUAL MONITORING AND REVIEW PROCEDURE SHALL BE PART OF THE ORGANIZATION'S COMPLIANCE PLAN. AN APPROPRIATE REPORT SHALL BE SUBMITTED TO THE EXECUTIVE BOARD CONCERNING ANY INTEREST DISCLOSED.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: COMPENSATION REVIEW OF TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIAL
GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE ORGANIZATION'S PROCESS FOR DETERMINING CEO COMPENSATION BEGINS WITH AN INITIATIVE LEAD BY THE CHAIRMAN OF THE GOVERNING BOARD. THE CHAIRMAN COMPARES COMPENSATION AND SALARY DATA WITH OTHER ORGANIZATION'S OF A SIMILAR SIZE AND INDUSTRY. THE CHAIRMAN REVIEWS THE DATA AND MAKES A RECOMMENDATION TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IN A CLOSED EXECUTIVE BOARD MEETING WHERE THE COMPENSATION IS THEN VOTED UPON BY ALL INDEPENDENT MEMBERS OF THE BOARD. THIS PROCESS WAS LAST COMPLETED IN MARCH 2008.
